=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"caption-side: bottom; --bs-table-bg:transparent; --bs-table-accent-bg:transparent; --bs-table-striped-color:#212529; --bs-table-striped-bg:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color:#212529; --bs-table-active-bg:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color:#212529; --bs-table-hover-bg:rgba(36, 41, 45, 0.075); width: 725.6px; vertical-align: top; background-color: transparent; border-spacing: 0px; font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><tbody><tr><th style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background: rgb(238, 238, 238); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">Sr.No.</th><th style=\"text-align: center; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background: rgb(238, 238, 238); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">UI Control &amp; Description</th></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">1</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\"><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/android/android_textview_control.htm\" alt=\"Android TextView Control\" style=\"color: rgb(49, 49, 49); transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; background-image: url(&quot;/images/link-icon.png&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat; padding-right: 22px; padding-bottom: 2px;\">TextView</a><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.6em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; line-height: 1.6;\">This control is used to display text to the user.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">2</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\"><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/android/android_edittext_control.htm\" alt=\"Android EditText Control\" style=\"color: rgb(49, 49, 49); transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; background-image: url(&quot;/images/link-icon.png&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat; padding-right: 22px; padding-bottom: 2px;\">EditText</a><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.6em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; line-height: 1.6;\">EditText is a predefined subclass of TextView that includes rich editing capabilities.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">3</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\"><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/android/android_autocompletetextview_control.htm\" alt=\"Android AutoCompleteTextView Control\" style=\"color: rgb(49, 49, 49); transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; background-image: url(&quot;/images/link-icon.png&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat; padding-right: 22px; padding-bottom: 2px;\">AutoCompleteTextView</a><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.6em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; line-height: 1.6;\">The AutoCompleteTextView is a view that is similar to EditText, except that it shows a list of completion suggestions automatically while the user is typing.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">4</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\"><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/android/android_button_control.htm\" alt=\"Android Button Control\" style=\"color: rgb(49, 49, 49); transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; background-image: url(&quot;/images/link-icon.png&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat; padding-right: 22px; padding-bottom: 2px;\">Button</a><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.6em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; line-height: 1.6;\">A push-button that can be pressed, or clicked, by the user to perform an action.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\">5</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.42857;\"><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/android/android_imagebutton_control.htm\" alt=\"Android ImageButton Control\" style=\"color: rgb(49, 49, 49); transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; background-image: url(&quot;/images/link-icon.png&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat; padding-right: 22px; padding-bottom: 2px;\">ImageButton</a><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.6em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; line-height: 1.6;\">An ImageButton is an AbsoluteLayout which enables you to specify the exact location of its children. This shows a button with an image (instead of text) that can be pressed or clicked by the user.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); padding: 8px; background-color: var(--bs-table-bg); box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 9999px var(--bs-table-accent-bg); line-height: 1.4285