3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This example shows a&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">bad combination</span>&nbsp;of text and background image. The text is hardly readable:&nbsp;</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate cssHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(4, 170, 109); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"cssselectorcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">body&nbsp;<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">{</span><span class=\"csspropertycolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;background-image<span class=\"csspropertyvaluecolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\"><span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">:</span>&nbsp;url(\"bgdesert.jpg\")<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">}</span></span></div></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left-width: initial; border-left-style: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;When using a background image, use an image that does not disturb the text.</p></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The background image can also be set for specific elements, like the &lt;p&gt; element:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 24px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate cssHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(4, 170, 109); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"cssselectorcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">p&nbsp;<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">{</span><span class=\"csspropertycolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;background-image<span class=\"csspropertyvaluecolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\"><span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">:</span>&nbsp;url(\"paper.gif\")<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">}</span></span></div></div><div><br></div>','CSS Background Image',101,6),(108,'<p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Margins are used to create space around elements, outside of any defined borders.</p><hr style=\"border-top-color: rgb(238, 238, 238); margin: 20px -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div class=\"w3-theme-border\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; margin: 70px; padding: 5px; border-color: rgb(4, 170, 109) !important;\">This element has a margin of 70px.</div><hr style=\"border-top-color: rgb(238, 238, 238); margin: 20px -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">CSS Margins</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The CSS&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">margin</code>&nbsp;properties are used to create space around elements, outside of any defined borders.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">With CSS, you have full control over the margins. There are properties for setting the margin for each side of an element (top, right, bottom, and left).</p><hr style=\"border-top-color: rgb(238, 238, 238); margin: 20px -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Margin - Individual Sides</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">CSS has properties for specifying the margin for each side of an element:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">margin-top</code></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">margin-right</code></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">margin-bottom</code></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">margin-left</code></li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">All the margin properties can have the following values:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">auto - the browser calculates the margin</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">length</em>&nbsp;- specifies a margin in px, pt, cm, etc.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">%</em>&nbsp;- specifies a margin in % of the width of the containing element</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">inherit - specifies that the margin should be inherited from the parent element</li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Tip:</span>&nbsp;Negative values are allowed.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 24px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Set different margins for all four sides of a &lt;p&gt; element:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate cssHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(4, 170, 109); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"cssselectorcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">p&nbsp;<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">{</span><span class=\"csspropertycolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;margin-top<span class=\"csspropertyvaluecolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\"><span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">:</span>&nbsp;100px<span class=\"cssdelimitercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\">;</span></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;margin-bottom<span class=\"csspropertyvaluecolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumb